%I A395589 #15 Jun 18 2026 19:38:50
%S A395589 1,2,7,61,2480,1373701
%N A395589 Number of 3-ary convexities on a set of n elements.
%C A395589 A convexity G on as set X is n-ary if its convex sets are precisely the sets A with the property that co(B) is a subset of A for each subset B with cardinality no more than n.
%D A395589 M. L. J. van de Vel, Theory of Convex Structures, North-Holland Mathematical Library, vol. 50, North-Holland, Amsterdam, 1993.
%H A395589 Aidar Dulliev and Daniil Naumikhin, <a href="https://arxiv.org/abs/2606.11252">Binomial Transform of Sequences Counting N-ary Convexities</a>, arXiv:2606.11252 [math.GM], 2026.
%H A395589 Daniil Naumikhin, <a href="https://github.com/SofaaSogo-oh/3gar-code">Enumeration of ternary Convex Structures</a>, GitHub repository.
%e A395589 For n=2 the a(2)=7 ternary convexities are following:
%e A395589   {{0, 1}, {}, {0}},
%e A395589   {{0, 1}, {0}},
%e A395589   {{0, 1}, {}, {1}},
%e A395589   {{0, 1}, {}},
%e A395589   {{0, 1}, {1}},
%e A395589   {{0, 1}, {}, {0}, {1}},
%e A395589   {{0, 1}}.
%Y A395589 Cf. A326878, A000798, A394095.
%K A395589 nonn,hard,more
%O A395589 0,2
%A A395589 _Daniil Naumikhin_, _Aidar Dulliev_, Jun 12 2026
